{
  "texts": [
    "Recent study has reported that students tend to express their concerns about privacy issues, ethical considerations, and ChatGPT's potential negative impact on learning and creativity if ChatGPT is fully allowed to be used in programming courses (Guner et al., 2024).",
    "The integration of AI tools, like ChatGPT, into educational settings has revealed the importance of diverse student interaction profiles with different levels of engagement (Koltovskaia et al., 2024; Lo et al., 2024), dependency (Haindl & Weinberger, 2024; Stojanov et al., 2024), and efficacy (Urban et al., 2024; Yilmaz & Yilmaz, 2023b) in using these technologies.",
    "Research has indicated that students interact with AI tools in distinct ways, which can be broadly categorized into different profiles based on their motivation and behaviors (Liu et al., 2024; Stojanov et al., 2024; Wang et al., 2023).",
    "For instance, some students may tend to utilize AI tools as a primary resource to get direct answers with a high level of dependency on AI (Liu et al., 2024; Stojanov et al., 2024).",
    "This can lead to increased efficiency in completing assignments but may also hinder the creativity and development of independent problem-solving skills (Gruenhagen et al., 2024)."
  ]
}